    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is mitigated by the FDA-accepted worst-case nature of the ASTM F1717 protocol and the two-laboratory experimental design. All three primary QoIs satisfy the pre-specified acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96; relative difference < 10%). The overall credibility package is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level conclusion for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw compression-bending COU.",
